    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme to cover all pregnant women",
        "additional_details": "I was forced to choose my job or my baby. As a Health care worker working in a care home and 13 weeks pregnant me and my employer made a decision for me to stop working as too many Residents were showing signs of Coronavirus.\r\n \r\nEveryday was making me more anxious about going to work worrying who I come in contact with might already have the virus.\r\n \r\nI couldn\u2019t be put on furlough so I had to go on sick pay which could result in me not being entitled to my maternity pay further down the line.",
        "background": "All Pregnant women at any stage of pregnancy to be entitled to the furlough scheme, especially people working in Health care.",
